    <section>
        <title>Advanced Configuration Properties</title>
        <para>
            This section covers the advanced properties which can be used to further
            configure the Wrapper.  These properties are not found in the default
            <literal moreinfo="none">wrapper.conf</literal> file distributed with the
            Wrapper.  However they can be added as needed.  The default values of these
            properties have been designed to work with the majority of applications.
            In most cases, they should not be changed.
        </para>
        <para>
            There are cases where they may need to be changed to suit the needs of a
            particular application.  When doing so however, please take the time to read
            the documentation of the property carefully and make sure that changing it is
            really what you want to do.
        </para>
        <warning>
            <simpara>
                Do not modify any of these parameters unless you have read
                the property description.  Incorrect settings can cause
                the Wrapper to fail to operate as expected.
            </simpara>
        </warning>
